    Dengue example

    Clean department codes of the disease data

    clean_depto_codes.Rd

    Function that cleans the department codes of the disease data

    Usage

    clean_depto_codes(disease_data, col_data_codes, geo_data, col_geo_codes)

    Arguments

    disease_data

    The disease data

    col_data_codes

    Column name in the disease data that contains the department codes

    geo_data

    Geographical data that includes the departments codes

    col_geo_codes

    Column name in the geographical data than contains the department codes

    Value

    Clean department codes of the disease data

    Examples

    geo_codes <- import_geo_codes()
disease_data <- import_linelist_disease_year(2019, "DENGUE")
clean_depto_codes(disease_data, 
                  col_data_codes = "cod_dpto_o", 
                  geo_codes, 
                  col_geo_codes = "c_digo_departamento")
